10 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
11 An Act relating to 2-1-1 services; creating the 2-1-1
Hotline Revolving Fund; specifying type of fund and
12 source of monies; stating purpose of the fund;
providing for expenditure of monies; providing for
13 codification; providing an effective date; and
declaring an emergency.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3022 of Title 56, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
21 fund for the Department of Human Services to be designated the “2-1-
22 1 Hotline Revolving Fund”. The fund shall be a continuing fund, not
23 subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall consist of all monies
24 received by the Department from legislative appropriations provided
Req. No. 17316 Page 1

1 for the purpose of maintaining a robust 2-1-1 system in this state.
2 All monies accruing to the credit of the fund are hereby
3 appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the Department for
4 the purpose provided for in this section. Expenditures from the
5 fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer
6 against claims filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the
7 Office of Management and Enterprise Services for approval and
8 payment.
9 B. No monies from the 2-1-1 Hotline Revolving Fund shall be
10 used to provide referrals, information, or assistance to any
11 organization, entity, or service that performs, promotes, or
12 facilitates abortions. Instead, the 2-1-1 system shall prioritize
13 referrals to crisis pregnancy centers, adoption agencies, and other
14 life-affirming resources that support expectant mothers and families
15 in choosing life. The Department of Human Services shall ensure
16 compliance with this subsection through annual audits and reporting
17 to the Legislature.
18 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
19 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
20 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
21 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
22 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
